# ------------------------------
# TPC-C benchmark (examples/tpc-c-benchmark)
# ------------------------------
# Codex review round 16 P2 fix: the nested examples/tpc-c-benchmark/.gitignore
# only protects this pattern relative to that directory -- invoking the CLI
# from the repo root (e.g. `node examples/tpc-c-benchmark/src/run.mjs seed`,
# without cd-ing into the example first) writes the default tenants file
# relative to the repo root instead, outside that nested rule's scope. This
# root-level rule covers plaintext tenant bearer tokens regardless of which
# directory the CLI happens to be invoked from.
